			<ns0:name>chris.ro...@gmail.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109476958443797771315/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">When the audio interface is first invoked with PpbAudioRpcServer::PPB_Audio_Create a new StreamCreatedCallbackData instance is created in the browser. If the NEXE module tears down the srpc channel before the stream has been created then a use after free condition will occur when the callback executes. The callback issues a call to PppAudioRpcClient::PPP_Audio_StreamCreated which calls NaClSrpcInvokeBySignature which dereferences the stale channel pointer when trying to make the following call:

NaClSrpcServiceMethodIndex(channel-&amp;gt;client, rpc_signature);

This is because the main srpc channel has already been torn down. You can trigger this bug by adding a simple call to exit(0) in the ppapi audio example ppapi_example_audio/audio.cc on line 206 after the TestSuite() function has completed, recompile the example, load it into the browser, it should crash/sad tab before you hear the test sound.

If other PPAPI interfaces have a similar callback mechanism they should be reviewed for similar bugs. I will take a look at them this week.
